Installing Sfark-convertor
=================

Requirements
------------

Sfark-convertor should work on any fairly recent GNU/Linux system, the following
dependencies are required:

    * python >= 2.7
    * kivy >= 1.1.0

Installation
------------

Sfark-convertor uses Python's distutils framework for installation. In order to
install Sfark-convertor, you will need root access. To install Sfark-convertor, perform
the following command as root:

      $ python setup.py install

Run Sfark-convertor
-----------

If you installed Sfark-convertor using the setup.py script, you can launch the
program by typing "Sfark-convertor" at the command line.
